Description: Lip sherd of North Ionian Middle or Late Wild Goat Style pottery oinochoe; exterior glazed with part of eye and eyebrow in added white; ridge at top of neck, with reserved area below; interior reserved.
School/style: Wild Goat Style (Middle II to late)
Curator's comments: Object owned and held by the Museum of Classical Archaeology, Cambridge. This record is included in the British Museum database as part of the Museum’s Naukratis Project, a research collaboration that aims to virtually re-unite finds from the ancient port city of Naukratis, now distributed over 80 museums worldwide.

For parallels, see British Museum 1907,1201.691; Cambridge NA39, Copenhagen 5607 in Cook and Dupont, 1998, p. 55, fig. 8.20. See also Rhodes 11544 in CVA, Rodi, Museo Archeologico Dello Spedale Dei Cavalieri 2, II.D.H.1, Pl.(475) 7.1
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.622)
